menu "breadboard: bb_wifi (routes)"

config BB_WIFI_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-init WiFi STA via bb_registry EARLY tier"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_wifi self-registers in the EARLY tier via
        BB_REGISTRY_REGISTER_EARLY so bb_registry_init_early() calls
        bb_wifi_init_sta() automatically. Disable if the application
        drives WiFi init manually (e.g. provisioning mode, AP mode,
        or custom retry policy).

config BB_WIFI_RETRY_FOREVER_WHEN_VALIDATED
    bool "Retry wifi forever when OTA is validated"
    default y
    depends on BB_WIFI_AUTOREGISTER
    help
      When the running firmware has been validated (bb_ota_is_validated()
      is true), bb_wifi_autoinit retries the STA connect indefinitely on
      cold-boot timeout instead of falling back to AP mode. A network
      outage shouldn't wipe credentials on a known-good build. Disable
      this if you want strict timeout-then-AP behavior even for validated
      firmware.

config BB_WIFI_ROUTES_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register /api/wifi and /api/scan HTTP routes via bb_registry"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_wifi self-registers GET /api/wifi (driver state +
        connection diagnostics) and GET /api/scan (async scan results) through
        bb_registry. The wifi driver init APIs (bb_wifi_init, _init_sta,
        _ensure_netif, etc.) stay caller-driven regardless of this flag.

config BB_WIFI_RECONFIGURE
    bool "Enable runtime wifi reconfigure + pending-creds try on boot"
    default y
    help
        Enables bb_wifi_reconfigure() which stages new credentials and reboots
        to try them. On boot, if pending creds get an IP they are committed as
        the new live credentials. On timeout the pending creds are cleared and
        the device reboots onto the prior live creds without incrementing
        boot_count. When disabled bb_wifi_reconfigure() returns BB_ERR_UNSUPPORTED
        and the autoinit path is byte-for-byte identical to the baseline.

config BB_WIFI_PENDING_TRY_TIMEOUT_S
    int "Bounded connect timeout for a runtime wifi reconfigure try (seconds)"
    default 30
    range 10 120
    depends on BB_WIFI_RECONFIGURE
    help
        Maximum time (seconds) to wait for an IP when attempting to connect
        with pending (staged) credentials. On timeout the pending creds are
        discarded, the device reboots onto the prior live credentials, and
        boot_count is NOT incremented.

choice BB_WIFI_POWER_SAVE
    prompt "WiFi power-save mode"
    default BB_WIFI_PS_MIN_MODEM
    help
        WiFi modem power-save. MIN_MODEM (default) sleeps the radio between
        beacons to save power but can cause beacon-miss/idle disconnects on
        quiet links; NONE keeps the radio always on for best link stability
        (recommended for mains-powered/always-on devices like miners).
    config BB_WIFI_PS_NONE
        bool "None (radio always on)"
    config BB_WIFI_PS_MIN_MODEM
        bool "Minimum modem sleep"
    config BB_WIFI_PS_MAX_MODEM
        bool "Maximum modem sleep"
endchoice

endmenu
